df.def%>% nrow()
## [1] 990

Number of participants in the final dataset that failed the manipulation check:

df.def %>% nrow() - df.def %>% filter(manipulation.check=="1") %>% nrow()
## [1] 437

Which is:

percent(df.def %>% filter(manipulation.check!="1") %>% nrow() / df.def %>% nrow(), accuracy = 0.01)
## [1] "44.14%"

give.n <- function(x){
  return(c(y = mean(x)*1.1, label = length(x))) 
}

6 Descriptive statistics


6.1 Demography

Age

age.population <- read.csv("AGE_FR-08022021.csv")
agecut.5 <- c(-Inf, 25, 30, 35, 40, 45, 50, 55, 60, 65, 70, 75, 80, Inf)


age.population <- age.population %>% mutate(agecat = case_when(age < 25 ~ "younger than 25",
          age >= 25 & age < 30 ~ "25-29",
          age >= 30 & age < 35 ~ "30-34",
          age >= 35 & age < 40 ~ "35-39",
          age >= 40 & age < 45 ~ "40-44",
          age >= 45 & age < 50 ~ "45-49",
          age >= 50 & age < 55 ~ "50-54",
          age >= 55 & age < 60 ~ "55-59",
          age >= 60 & age < 65 ~ "60-64",
          age >= 65 & age < 70 ~ "65-69",
          age >= 70 & age < 75 ~ "70-74",
          age >= 75 & age < 80 ~ "75-79",
          age >= 80 ~ "80 or older"))
  
age.population.5 <- age.population %>% group_by(agecat) %>% tally(count) %>% mutate(percentage = n / sum(n))

age.total <- merge(age.population.5, age.sample, by.x = "agecat", by.y = ".")

age.total <- age.total %>% 
  rename(age.category = agecat,
  count.population = n.x,
  count.sample = n.y,
  percentage.population = percentage.x,
  percentage.sample = percentage.y)

age.total$age.category <- factor(age.total$age.category, levels = c(
"younger than 25",
"25-29",           "30-34",           "35-39",          
"40-44",           "45-49",           "50-54",          
"55-59",           "60-64",           "65-69",          
"70-74",           "75-79",           "80 or older"))    

age.total %>% select(age.category, percentage.population, percentage.sample) %>% reshape2::melt(id.vars = 'age.category', variable.name = 'series')  %>% ggplot(aes(age.category, value, colour = series, fill = series)) + geom_bar (stat="identity", width=0.9, position = position_dodge(width=0.9)) + 
  theme_blank() + theme(legend.position="top", axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1), axis.title  = element_blank()) + scale_y_continuous(labels=scales::percent)
